
[1]declaratory

   DECLAR'ATORY, a. Making declaration, clear manifestation, or
   exhibition; expressive; as, this clause is declaratory of the will of
   the legislature. The declaratory part of a law, is that which sets
   forth and defines what is right and what is wrong. A declaratory act,
   is an act or statute which sets forth more clearly and explains the
   intention of the legislature in a former act.

   DECLA'RE, v.t. [L. to make clear.]
